.TH JULIETBENCH 1 "2026-04-19" "maneater-bench" "Maneater Bench Fixtures"
.SH NAME
julietbench \- deterministic bench fixture command number 10
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B julietbench
[\fIOPTION\fR]... [\fIFILE\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B julietbench
utility is fixture number 10 in the bench-manpath corpus. It exists to
exercise the mandoc + pandoc rendering pipeline with deterministic roff
source so wall-clock measurements are reproducible across runs of the
bench recipe. Each fixture page has distinct NAME / SYNOPSIS /
DESCRIPTION content so the embedding index does not collapse them to a
single entry.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v " " \-\-verbose
Print verbose output for fixture 10.
.TP
.BR \-q " " \-\-quiet
Suppress non-essential output for fixture 10.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Exercise fixture 10 in default mode:
.PP
.nf
.RS
julietbench alpha.txt bravo.txt
.RE
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR maneater (1)
